Problem-231(Power of two)

Description:
Given an integer n, return true if it is a power of two. Otherwise, return false.
An integer n is a power of two, if there exists an integer x such that n == 2x.

Example 1:
Input: n = 1
Output: true
Explanation: 20 = 1

Example 2:
Input: n = 16
Output: true
Explanation: 24 = 16

Example 3:
Input: n = 3
Output: false

Constraints:
-231 <= n <= 231 - 1

Solution:
bool isPowerOfTwo(int n) {
    int count=0;
    int count1=0;
    while(n!=0){
        if(n%2==0){
            n/=2;
            count1++;
        }
        else if(n==1){
            return true;
        }
        else 
        return false;
    }
   if(count1>1){
       return true;
   }
   else return false;
}
